<collectingCountry id="F36CB58FFFD2784378C21772FE252F59" box="[395,485,352,378]" name="Mexico" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(not available for examination). 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B8E9CFFD278437A241772FBAC2F5A" box="[877,1132,352,377]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Opoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="staudingeri">
<emphasis id="B90F290DFFD278437A241772FBAC2F5A" box="[877,1132,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Opoptera staudingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species of the genus for which a description of early stages has been published (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA88EEFFD278437ADE179AFBFF2F81" author="DeVries" box="[919,1087,392,418]" pageId="12" pageNumber="16" refString="DeVries, P. J. (1987) The Butterflies of Costa Rica and their Natural History. Princeton University Press, Princeton, New Jersey. 327 p." type="book" year="1987">
DeVries 
<number id="3DB3E738FFD278437D49179AFBFF2F81" box="[1024,1087,392,418]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1987.0">1987</number>
</bibRefCitation>
